HEADWORD: Emblematical
<hw>Em`blem*at"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>embl⟦eacute⟧matique</ets>.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to, containing,
or consisting in, an emblem; symbolic; typically representative;
representing as an emblem; <as>as, <ex>emblematic</ex> language or
ornaments; a crown is <ex>emblematic</ex> of royalty; white is
<ex>emblematic</ex> of purity.</as></def> --
<wordforms><wf>Em`blem*at"ic*al*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

